records.nl_statement: Let $E$ be a bounded set in $R^{1}$. Prove that there exists a real function $f$ such that $f$ is uniformly continuous and is not bounded on $E$.
records.lean_header:

open scoped BigOperators

  (E : Set ℝ) (h : Bornology.IsBounded E) :
  ∃ f : ℝ → ℝ, UniformContinuousOn f E ∧ ¬ Bornology.IsBounded (Set.image f E) :=
